(* ### Problem

 \]Next, $.\overline{03}$: \[ 99 \cdot .\overline{03} = (100-1) \cdot .\overline{03} = 3.\overline{03} - .\overline{03} = 3\\ \Rightarrow .\overline{03} = \frac{3}{99} = \frac{3}{3 \cdot 33} = \frac{1}{33}.
 \]We now have the tools to make our calculation: \begin{align} .0\overline{3} \div .\overline{03} &= \frac{1}{30} \div \frac{1}{33}= \frac{1}{30} \cdot \frac{33}{1}\\ &= \frac{33}{30} = \frac{3 \cdot 11}{3 \cdot 10} = \frac{11}{10}\\
 &= \frac{10+1}{10} = \boxed{1\frac{1}{10}}. \end{align}
 *)
